Summary
--------

- Usual way of authentication is username and password.

- HTTPS is stateless.

- Session cookies are used to persist the user's session at the server.

- Broken Authentication system can lead to data leak of a using client's or even the server admin.

- Reasons to be vulnerable with this...
	- Bruteforce attacks

	- Weak Password Policies

	- Weak Session Cookies

- Counter-Measures...
	- Implement strong password policy

	- Lockout condition against bruteforce attacks.

	- Multi-Factor Authentication